SUMMARY:Jump
DESCRIPTION:90 minutes | English and Hindi | Mature Content for Ages 16+ \nTrigger Warnings: Suicide & Self Harm \nA two-actor black comedy about life\, death\, and everything in between. A successful female executive is ready to commit suicide by jumping off a roof when a male cab driver saves her. \nThis sets the stage for a collision between two completely opposite worlds\, personalities\,\ncircumstances\, beliefs\, and perspectives. Despite their contrasting socio-economic classes\, backgrounds\, and lifestyles\, this unusual encounter leads to a night of pure and simple human connection. \nWill the man be able to truly save her\, or will she be back to jump again? \nThe play explores the themes of suicide\, depression\, loneliness\, happiness\, love\, having or not having a purpose in life\, and ultimately death\, creating an emotionally complex and thought-provoking experience for the audience. Jump delves into the human psyche\, showcasing the struggles\, challenges\, and aspirations of two very different individuals who would never meet in normal circumstances but find a unique connection in the most unexpected of places and in their shared\nhumanity. \nDirector’s Note \nApart from being an actor and director\, I’m also a mountaineer. I was in an advanced mountaineering course trying to summit a Himalayan mountain in October 2022. An avalanche came\, and we lost 29 people out of a batch of 53 people. I somehow survived the incident and escaped death. The incident changed me\, my core beliefs\, and my perspective on living life. For the first time\, I felt depressed and tried therapy. The incident left me with a lot of questions. WHO recently declared loneliness a ‘global public health concern’. In India\, 1 in every 5 individuals suffers from some form of mental health illness\, and over 2.6 lakh cases of suicide occur in a year. \nGiven these alarming numbers\, considering and addressing mental health is still at a very early stage in India. In a post-pandemic world\, the alarming rise in suicide\, depression\, and loneliness rates around the world shows that our pursuit of success and materialistic goals doesn’t lead us to genuine happiness and fulfilment. In the world of social media\, because of personal\, sociological\, political\, and geographical reasons\, we feel disconnected more than ever before. We often witness instances where seemingly successful and happy individuals suddenly take their own lives. In spite of the number of self-help books\, motivational speakers\, and influencers preaching about finding life’s purpose\, a significant portion of us are just trying to survive. \nOur individual perspectives play a significant role in shaping our lives. We tend to surround ourselves with like-minded people who share similar perspectives. We believe that our own perspective is the\nultimate and only valid one. If we look closely enough\, all the conflicts in the world are just a clash of different and opposing perspectives. \nThe essence of Jump lies in the meeting of these two contrasting characters\, identities\, perspectives\, lifestyles\, and worlds within a highly unusual situation. \nAbout Collective Madness\nEvery project for us is an attempt to find a unique connection with our audience around the ideas we believe in. Collective Madness Studios\, established in 2004\, is a platform for anyone who believes that theatre is a practicing art form and provides a space for those who are passionately attached to theatre. The studio has produced close to 20 projects\, including musicals\, adaptations and plays with social messages We believe in collaboration & experiential learning. It is at the heart of all our products & initiatives. Every individual human experience is a limiting one\, so collaborating with others has become essential. Collaborations challenge one’s current understandings and help to see things from new perspectives. \nCast and Crew: \nActors: Vidushi Chadha and Sandeep Shikhar\nWriter & Director: Maneesh Verma\nDramaturg: Akhshay Gandhi\nAssociate Director & Lights: Vishal\nScenography: Maneesh Verma and Dhanendra Kawade\nProduction Manager: Monika Gupta\nSoundscape: Sahil Vaid\nSong Music Producer: Kaizad Gherda\nSong Lyrics & Music: Asif Ali Beg\nSong Singer: Shazneen Arethna\nProduced by Collective Madness Studios\nSpecial Thanks Kalyani Hiwale\, Harsh Khurana\, Tushar Pandey \nJump is inspired from “Umbrella” written by Larry Pontius\nCommissioned by Serendipity Arts Festival 2023 \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/jump/
